text.section:
Any resolution authorizing any bonds may contain provisions, which shall be a part of the contract with the holders of the bonds, as to:
Pledging all or any part of the gross or net revenues of the district to secure the payment of the bonds and interest on the bonds;
The amounts to be raised in each year by rates, rentals, and charges, and their use and disposition, and of any other revenues of the district;
The setting aside of reserves or sinking funds and their regulation and disposition;
Limitations on the right of the district to restrict and regulate the use of its facilities;
Limitations on the purposes to which the proceeds of sale of any issue of bonds to be issued may be applied;
Limitations on the issuance of additional bonds; and
The procedure, if any, by which the term of any contract with bondholders may be amended or abrogated, the amount of bonds the holders of which must consent, and the manner in which the consent may be given.
